<br>
I loved Velious and the way its encounters were implimented, but everything I've read about high level SOL makes me never want to play again.<br>
<br>
I can understand SOE's point of view.. kinda..  /played is probably the biggest difference between the average player and the 'uber' player.  <br>
<br>
Velious was fun as hell, but look how accessable it became.  As time consuming as it was, guilds of average players were able to eventually do things the things that uber guilds were capable of, creating the conflict that eventually followed every EQ release -- fights over planes, trak/vs, and velious boss mobs including tov and ntov.<br>
<br>
I think that SOE really wanted to create content that top guilds would have to themselves, that would be a massive challenge to acheive, that would truly separate the average player from the uber player and perhaps keep them from conflicts.<br>
<br>
Obviously high level EQ doesn't have a high barrier of entry in terms of skill.  It's about being competent, equipped, having time and knowing the strategy.  The strats don't stay secret for very long, and once leaked, spread like mad. <br>
<br>
What was said for skill can also be applied to intelligence.  Using quests with tough puzzles doesn't work as they tend to be spoiled so quickly.<br>
<br>
SOE couldn't make encounters require more skill or brains so they made them more time consuming, pushing the true barrier of entry of the elite up another notch. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucerosofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceros of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 618<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/29/02 10:32:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2472.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Interesting Point of View on SoL and timesinks.</span><hr size=1> I don't mean to say that there is no such thing as skill in EQ.  Playing in IV, I met a lot of people who were excellent with their classes, some of the best players who I've ever seen.<br>
