It's also in SOE's best interests to keep dedicated players away from the average EQ players.  EQ sucks for the player who plays 20 hours a week when he has to compete with the players who play 50 hours a week for the same mobs.  We saw that a lot in the original game, Kunark and eventually SoV -- though, not for a while. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucerosofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceros of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 624<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/30/02 4:20:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2472.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Interesting Point of View on SoL and timesinks.</span><hr size=1> As for the issues that uber guilds present falling on deaf ears, I disagree.  Verant has reacted in adjusting aspects of uber encounters in the past based on feedback and have already said that there are issues with SOL uber encounter drops that they're working on fixing.<br>
<br>
Listening to feedback doesn't mean changing everything that people don't like of course.<br>
<br>
The whining regarding Trak was due to spawn competition, not that he was too hard or too time consuming.  At least by the top guilds..  that's how I remember it at least, and I was paying a lot of attention to such things at the time, especially regarding Soul Assassins on Lanys which took Trak down pretty quickly relative to some older servers.<br>
