<br>
And honestly the no lives ect ect rhetoric gets pretty tiresome, enspecially considering that the time sinks are not really dependent on spending alot of time in a row, they are almost all the xp camps that you love so much.  If it was clearing pog to get a key you might have a case, but theres really nothing logically requiring that you have no life to camp a key. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uciliemvaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ciliem Vaz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/30/02 5:10:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2472.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.msu.edu/user/cooking3/dm/cil2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Interesting Point of View on SoL and timesinks.</span><hr size=1> The point of the timesinks is to keep the guilds busy.  It's the same reason they make you clear PoF or PoG before you attempt Tunare or CT, because it keeps you busy for longer.  If you consider it, it's actually intelligent and makes the game more fun for everyone.<br>
<br>
Obviously, there are a few select guilds with the most &quot;raw power&quot; and these are the guilds now that just go rape whatever nameds are rumored to be up and take the most content away from others who might need to gather in advance.  <br>
<br>
What they are trying to avoid, in my view, is Lodizal.  These are the mobs that take seconds to kill, occupy nobody for very long , yet drop awesome loot.  These mobs have never kept anyone busy for any real period of time and just get assraped as soon as they pop.  If you put in a timesink then you occupy a group of people (like Triton for example) that would be blowing up every named the second after it pops.  If you are not in the top guild on your server, then the timesinks are giving you opportunities you may have never had access to before.  <br>
<br>
Before you complain, remember, nobody has to do this stuff -- its like the VP key.  Go, or don't go, but if you're -really- uber... It's an appeal to the macho side of these 'we've done it all' guilds.  Of course they will do it, but they realize its costing them and they think about how many nameds they could have broken off...<br>
